<P>
U.S. COPTER HITS TREE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
PANAMA CITY 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A U.S. Army pilot guided his damaged helicopter to a safe landing at Ft. 
</P>
<P>
Sherman after hitting a tree, the U.S. Southern Command said Tuesday. The five 
crew members were not injured. 
</P>
<P>
The helicopter, a CH-47D Chinook on a routine training exercise, was 
approaching the landing strip Monday at the fort. 
</P>
