<HEADLINE>
<P>
GRATEFUL TO SUPERVISORS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I wish to publicly express gratitude to Supervisors Mike Antonovich, Pete 
Schabarum, and Deane Dana for denying a petitioner's request for a zoning 
change at the Lost Hills Business Center. 
</P>
<P>
Their denial of the change prevented a defense contractor from opening a 
gyroscope-manufacturing business in which hazardous chemicals, gases and toxic 
wastes would have been stored near homes and A.E. Wright Middle School, where 
1,250 students are enrolled. 
</P>
<P>
I want to thank the supervisors for their insight in recognizing the potential 
risks this change represented and their wisdom in denying the petitioner's 
request. 
</P>
<P>
SHARON BROWN 
</P>
<P>
Woodland Hills 
</P>
<P>
Brown is president of A.E. Wright Middle School Parent-Faculty Club 
</P>
</TEXT>
