<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO SPORTS ET CETERA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GOLF 
</P>
<P>
San Diego State (867) won the Grand Canyon University Invitational, finishing 
ahead of second-place Texas Lutheran College (876) and third-place Cal State 
Northridge (883). 
</P>
<P>
SDSU's Kevin Riley won the individual bracket with a 208, 71 in the first 
round, 69 in the second and 68 in the third. 
</P>
<P>
Aztecs Mike Jun (221) and Tim Todd (221) were among four players tied for 
eighth. 
</P>
<P>
USIU's Tracy Marble shot a 75 on the second day of the Arizona State 
Invitational to move from 45th place to 21st. Marble, who shot 80 Monday, has a 
155 total going into today's final round. USIU's women are 12th in the team 
competition, SDSU 15th. 
</P>
<P>
WOMEN'S TENNIS 
</P>
<P>
Point Loma Nazarene swept Cal State San Bernardino, 9-0, in an NAIA District 3 
match. At No. 1 singles, Kim Wright defeated Erin Kaskey, 6-3, 6-0, for PLNC 
(9-7). Wright then teamed with Shannon Anderson to defeat Kaskey and Chris 
Ballesteros, 6-1, 6-1, at No. 1 doubles. Cal State Bernardino is 6-11. 
</P>
<P>
SOFTBALL 
</P>
<P>
San Diego State was swept in a Big West doubleheader by No. 2-ranked Fresno 
State, 8-1 and 3-0. SDSU's Jennifer Droback was 2 for 2 in the first game; the 
Aztecs (13-24, 4-11) managed just one hit in the second. Fresno State is 40-7, 
19-2. 
</P>
