<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO SPORTS ET CETERA: DOANE'S THIRD HOMER RALLIES USD TO VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CURT HOLBREICH 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Rick Doane hit a three-run home run -- his third of the game -- in the bottom 
of the ninth to give the University of San Diego an 8-7 victory over visiting 
Pacific Lutheran (11-9) Tuesday. Doane's other home runs were with the bases 
empty in the first and fifth innings. 
</P>
<P>
Doane, a junior and Clairemont High graduate, has nine home runs. 
</P>
<P>
Freshman Kevin Herde, a San Pasqual graduate, had three hits, including two 
doubles, for USD (17-22). 
</P>
<P>
U.S. International snapped a 13-game losing streak by defeating UC Irvine, 
12-6, at USIU. USIU (10-31-1), led by a two-run homer by Geoff Martinez, came 
from a 5-4 deficit by scoring five runs in the bottom of the seventh. 
</P>
<P>
Beto Rodriguez hit a three-run homer in the first inning to give USIU a 3-1 
lead. Irvine is 23-16. 
</P>
<P>
FOOTBALL 
</P>
<P>
The Chargers were notified by the Indianapolis Colts that they will receive the 
Colts' third-round draft pick this year as part of the trade that sent 
linebacker Chip Banks to Indianapolis midway through last season. 
</P>
<P>
The Colts had the option of giving the Chargers their third-round pick this 
year or their second-round choice in 1991. Tuesday was the deadline for 
notifying the Chargers of their decision. The Chargers now have two picks in 
the third round. CURT HOLBREICH 
</P>
</TEXT>
