<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGH SCHOOL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
MONTCLAIR PREP POWER SHOCKS EL CAMINO REAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By VINCE KOWALICK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Home runs by Keyaan Cook and Dylan Jones knocked El Camino Real High from the 
ranks of the unbeaten Tuesday as Montclair Prep posted a 7-6 victory in the 
semifinal round of the Thousand Oaks baseball tournament. 
</P>
<P>
Cook, a senior, belted a three-run home run off junior right-hander Terry 
Morrow (0-1) to give Montclair Prep a 3-0 first-inning lead. 
</P>
<P>
Jones, a junior designated-hitter, added a solo home run in the second inning. 
Montclair Prep (14-2) added three runs in the third. 
</P>
<P>
Senior right-hander Kevin Grant (7-1) scattered eight hits and stifled a 
seventh-inning rally for the win. With one out and runners at first and second, 
Gregg Sheren hit a fly ball to the warning track in center field. Both runners 
advanced on a wild pitch before Jason Cohen flied to left to end the game. 
</P>
<P>
Montclair Prep plays Agoura today at 1 p. m. for the tournament championship. 
</P>
<P>
In an earlier quarterfinal game, El Camino Real (10-1-1) scored 11 runs in the 
fourth inning en route to clobbering Canyon, 12-1. Junior right-hander Corey 
Bromberg (1-0) struck out eight while pitching a four-hitter. 
</P>
<P>
Cohen hit a three-run home run and Sheren had a solo homer. 
</P>
