<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Quarterback Jack Trudeau of the Indianapolis Colts was released on his own 
recognizance after his early-morning arrest on a charge of drunken driving. 
</P>
<P>
Trudeau, 27, of Carmel, Ind., was stopped by a Carmel police officer for 
speeding and erratic driving about 3 a.m. He recorded a blood-alcohol content 
of 0.19%, nearly twice Indiana's legal limit of 0.10%. 
</P>
</TEXT>
