<HEADLINE>
<P>
CYPRESS WINS VISALIA SOFTBALL TOURNAMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Collene Conahan hit a grand slam and Sally Dugas got her fourth victory in two 
days as Cypress College defeated Moorpark, 9-1, Tuesday in the championship 
game of the Visalia softball tournament that was shortened by the mercy rule. 
</P>
<P>
Conahan, who was named to the all-tournament team, hit her home run in the 
third inning to give Cypress (31-4) a 6-0 lead. 
</P>
<P>
Dugas (16-2), the tournament's most valuable player and pitcher, allowed two 
hits in three innings. Teresa Anderson, who went two for three with an run 
batted in and a stolen base, also was named to the all-tournament team. 
</P>
</TEXT>
