<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
USC SLIPS PAST CAL STATE FULLERTON IN NINTH, 6-5 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jeff Cirillo had an RBI single in the ninth inning to give USC a 6-5 victory 
over Cal State Fullerton Tuesday in a nonconference baseball game at Titan 
Field. 
</P>
<P>
Danny Gil opened the ninth with a double off Fullerton pitcher Matt Watson. 
Watson (1-5) struck out the next two hitters before Cirillo hit a slow roller 
through the left side. 
</P>
<P>
Fullerton had two runners on with two out in the ninth, but Eric Hughes got 
Matt Hattabaugh to fly out to center. Hughes (2-2) did not allow a run over the 
final two innings for the victory. 
</P>
<P>
Fullerton starter Huck Flener allowed four runs in 2/3 of an inning and USC 
(28-11) added another run in the third to take a 5-2 lead. 
</P>
<P>
Fullerton scored two in the second and three in the fifth. 
</P>
<P>
In the fifth, Phil Nevin led off with a double for the Titans (18-16). Rich 
Gonzales had an RBI single and scored on Paul Bunch's double. Bunch went to 
third on a passed ball and scored on a squeeze by Hattabaugh. 
</P>
<P>
In another nonconference baseball game: 
</P>
<P>
U.S. International 12, UC Irvine 6 -- Jon Damush had three hits, scored two 
runs and drove in another and Chris Gallego had three hits and two RBIs for 
visiting Irvine (23-17). USIU is 10-31. 
</P>
<P>
In Golden State Athletic Conference baseball: 
</P>
<P>
Cal Baptist 6, Southern California College 5 -- Tim Lopez hit a two-run single 
in the eighth inning and visiting Cal Baptist (25-8, 10-3) moved into first 
place in the conference. Denny Berni, who went three for four, hit a two-run 
homer in the fifth to tie the score, 4-4, and singled in a run in the seventh 
to give SCC (21-14, 9-4) a 5-4 lead. 
</P>
<P>
In nonconference softball: 
</P>
<P>
Christ College Irvine 5-0, Occidental 0-3 -- Lisa Merenda (11-8) pitched a 
four-hitter and Kathy Carroll had three hits and four RBIs in the first game 
for host Christ College Irvine (21-19). 
</P>
</TEXT>
