<HEADLINE>
<P>
VALENCIA'S TIDLAND WINS L.A. JUNIOR GOLF CHAMPIONSHIP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ENCINO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Chris Tidland of Valencia High School won the Los Angeles Junior Golf 
Championships Tuesday with a two-day score of 143 at the Sepulveda golf 
courses. 
</P>
<P>
Tidland, 17, shot a 70 Monday and trailed Jim Skinner of Pacific Palisades by a 
stroke. Skinner, however, shot an 80 Tuesday and Tidland, who shot 73, was 
never challenged. 
</P>
<P>
Tidland, who won the Southern Section individual championship last season, 
plans to attend Oklahoma State on a golf scholarship in the fall. 
</P>
</TEXT>
