<P>
UAL Signs Buyout Deal: UAL Corp. signed an agreement to be bought for $4.4 
billion by a group of its unions, but analysts remain skeptical that the 
largest-ever U.S. employee-led buyout will succeed. The stock has languished 
far below the $201-a-share of the employee group's bid, reflecting the 
widespread doubts. On Tuesday, it finished up 25 cents to $161.25 on the NYSE. 
</P>
