<TEXT>
<P>
Heinz Will Use Recyclable Plastic Bottles: H. J. Heinz Co. said it will begin 
making ketchup squeeze bottles from polyethylene terephthalate (PET), which can 
be recycled, rather than the existing composite of polypropylene and adhesives. 
Environmentalists generally supported the move while cautioning that until 
plastic recycling markets are in place, the new bottles will continue to meet 
the fate of the old: burial in a landfill. 
</P>
