<P>
AT&amp;T Selling Terminals Business: American Telephone &amp; Telegraph Co. 
said it is selling one of its terminal equipment businesses to Memorex Telex 
Corp., the U.S. subsidiary of a leading Dutch computer manufacturer. Financial 
terms of the acquisition were not disclosed. The acquisition covers AT&amp;T's 
synchronous terminal products unit, which includes a line of computer equipment 
used to connect various terminals and a specific line of mainframes 
manufactured by IBM or IBM-compatible versions. 
</P>
