BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CBOT Cleared in Soybean Flap: The Chicago Board of Trade acted within ethics 
rules when it declared an emergency and ordered traders to reduce July, 1989, 
soybean holdings, the General Accounting Office said. The GAO concluded that 
Board of Trade members who held contracts did not participate in meetings that 
led to the emergency order. The controversy centered on Ferruzzi Finanziaria 
SpA, one of the world's largest soybean processors. 
</P>
