executive producer of NBC Sports and the current executive producer of the 
now-canceled "Pat Sajak Show," is developing a new late-night show for CBS that 
is scheduled to debut this summer in the 12:30 a.m. time slot. Weisman took 
control of the beleaguered CBS talk show last January. Of the low-rated 
"Sajak," which will air for the last time Friday, Weisman said, "It is ironic 
that we will have our last show on Good Friday, but as one of my writers said: 
'Yeah, but on Easter Sunday, we won't be coming back.' " GREG BRAXTON 
