<TEXT>
<P>
The Brea Civic and Cultural Center Gallery is calling for entries from artists 
working in all media for "The Real Thing," a representational art exhibit that 
will open May 12. 
</P>
<P>
The juror is Louis Newman, director of Louis Newman Galleries in Beverly Hills. 
Awards totaling $650 and purchase awards will be presented, and winning artists 
will be encouraged to offer their work for sale. Hand-delivered entries will be 
accepted at the gallery, Number One Civic Center Circle, on April 20 and 21. 
The fee is $6 per entry; free for the first two pieces submitted by each Brea 
artist. For information and entry forms, call (714) 990-7730. 
