<P>
SOVIET DIPLOMAT FOUND SHOT TO DEATH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Stasis Obukauskas, 41, second secretary and consul at the Soviet Embassy in 
Suriname, was found shot to death, his body lying in a gutter in Paramaribo, 
capital of the South American nation, police said. 
</P>
<P>
No group or individual claimed responsibility for the killing, and the motive 
was unknown. Obukauskas had been in Suriname about 2 1/2 years. There was no 
comment from the Soviet Embassy. Suriname gained independence from the 
Netherlands in 1975. 
</P>
