<P>
$3 MILLION STOLEN IN RECORD TRAIN HEIST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Train robbers shot and killed a postal worker and stole $3 million in Austrian 
currency from a mail car in what police said was the biggest heist in the 
history of Austria's postal service. The robbery near Vienna prompted postal 
authorities to post a $25,600 reward for the three thieves. The bandits stole 
moneybags containing about 35 million Austrian schillings before walking off 
the train unnoticed when it stopped in the suburb of Huetteldorf. 
</P>
