<HEADLINE>
<P>
FOR THE RECORD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CRA policies -- A headline in a Times story March 31 may have created the 
erroneous impression that accounting firm owner Deborah Morrisette had 
criticized the Community Redevelopment Agency during a workshop for minority- 
and women-owned businesses. Additionally, a sentence in the story implied that 
Morrisette was critical of practices that permitted Bishop H.H. Brookins and 
other influential members of minorities to get city contracts. Morrissette made 
no such statement regarding Brookins. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Correction 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
