Carl Perkins earned his Ph.D. in rock 'n' roll long ago and now he'll get an 
honorary doctor of humanities from Lambuth College in Jackson, Tenn., on April 
29. When Lambuth President Thomas Boyd called to talk to Perkins about the 
degree, Perkins asked him, "Can you graduate from college with only eight years 
in school?" Thomas assured him that he could, in this case. . . . There's 
another Kennedy wedding coming up in the fall. 
