<P>
TURNER STATION SKIPS THE BRAVES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ATLANTA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TV viewers who hoped to see Dale Murphy and Will Clark start the baseball 
season were seeing Herman Munster and Jed Clampett instead, thanks to a spring 
thunderstorm and programming decisions at SuperStation TBS. 
</P>
<P>
Ted Turner's television station, WTBS, decided not to show the opener of 
Turner's baseball team, the Atlanta Braves, this afternoon. 
</P>
<P>
The season opener, against the National League champion San Francisco Giants, 
was scheduled to be televised from Atlanta Tuesday night, but a strong 
thunderstorm washed out the game. 
</P>
<P>
A 5:10 p.m. EDT double-header was then scheduled for today, but a TBS Sports 
spokeswoman said there are no plans to change the programming to televise 
either game. 
</P>
<P>
The TBS lineup tonight: "The Munsters," "The Beverly Hillbillies" and the 
Atlanta Hawks-Milwaukee Bucks basketball game. 
